As often happens in calculus, the sum is replaced by an integral so that the \
inner product between two functions ",
 StyleBox["f",
  FontSlant->"Italic"],
 "(",
 StyleBox["t",
  FontSlant->"Italic"],
 ") and ",
 StyleBox["g",
  FontSlant->"Italic"],
 "(",
 StyleBox["t",
  FontSlant->"Italic"],
 ") is given by "
}], "Text",
 CellChangeTimes->{{3.5454731947421*^9, 
  3.545473228693132*^9}},ExpressionUUID->"428e31f9-c1ff-4276-80ee-\
e30acbb6590a"],

Cell[BoxData[
 FormBox[
  RowBox[{
   RowBox[{"<", 
    RowBox[{"f", 
     RowBox[{"(", "t", ")"}]}]}], ",", 
   RowBox[{
    RowBox[{
     RowBox[{"g", "(", "t", ")"}], ">"}], "=", 
    RowBox[{
     SubsuperscriptBox["\[Integral]", 
      RowBox[{"-", "\[Infinity]"}], "\[Infinity]"], 
     RowBox[{
      RowBox[{"f", "(", "t", ")"}], 
      RowBox[{"g", "(", "t", ")"}], 
      RowBox[{"\[DifferentialD]", "t"}]}]}]}]}], TraditionalForm]], "Text",
 CellChangeTimes->{{3.545472010328538*^9, 3.5454722023876553`*^9}, {
   3.545472232740546*^9, 3.545472306460702*^9}, {3.545472816157428*^9, 
   3.5454728616631823`*^9}, {3.5454730116326313`*^9, 3.5454731761434183`*^9}, 
   3.545473235624776*^9},ExpressionUUID->"88e881f1-893b-4af8-bee2-\
fae955602782"],

Cell[TextData[{
 "The next demonstration directly calculates this integral for a variety of \
functions. This is based on \[OpenCurlyDoubleQuote]Orthogonality of Two \
Functions with Weighted Inner Products\[CloseCurlyDoubleQuote] from the \
Wolfram Demonstrations \
Project\[NonBreakingSpace]http://demonstrations.wolfram.com/\
OrthogonalityOfTwoFunctionsWithWeightedInnerProducts/ by Alain Goriely. \
Observe how Sin[",
 StyleBox["nx",
  FontSlant->"Italic"],
 "] is orthogonal to Sin[",
 StyleBox["mx",
  FontSlant->"Italic"],
 "] except for the special case when ",
 StyleBox["n=m",
  FontSlant->"Italic"],
 "."
}], "Text",
 CellChangeTimes->{{3.5454732646272097`*^9, 3.5454732889497633`*^9}, {
